r.txt Ohm's law

S:cross section
l:characteristic length
I:current
e:electron
n:quantity of electron
v:velocity for electric current
q:electric charge
t:time
V:voltage
E:electric fields (E = V/l)
m:mass electron
k:resistivity at velocity 
C:arbitary constant for integlation
p:index for resistance 
R:resistance


*current
I = neSv

q = It = neV = neSl
I = q/t

v = l/t
l = vt

q = neSl = nSvte

q/t = neSv = I

therefore I = neSv



*V=IR
m a = -e E - kv

m dv/dt = -e E - kv

dv/dt = (-e E - kv)/m = -k/m(v + (e E)/k)

1/(v + (e E)/k) dv = -k/m dt

log (v + (e E)/k) = -kt/m + C

v = +/-exp(-kt/m + C) - (e E)/k = +/-exp(C)exp(-kt/m) - (e E)/k = C'exp(-kt/m) - (e E)/k

t -> 0, v = (e E)/k, -> C' = -(e E)/k

v = (e E)/k (1 - exp(-kt/m))

lim(t->inf)v = (e E)/k

E = V/l

I = neSv = neS (e E)/k = (ne^2 S V)/(k l) 

V = I k/(n e^2) (l/S)

p = k/(e^2 n)

R = p(l/S)

V = I k/(n e^2) (l/S) = I p(l/S) = IR

therefore V = IR

